body:
`customResolver` option is mostly just an alternative way of writing
```js
const plugin = {
  name: 'my-plugin',
  resolveId(id, importer) {
    // code
  }
}
```
. Also it isn't implemented in the native alias plugin and causes the build to be slower than using a custom plugin with hook filter.

Since it's not common, I think we should remove this option.

